All Classes

  • All Classes Interface Summary Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddIngredientFragment
    Fragment that handles adding/editing a StorageIngredient.
    AddIngredientFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener
    Listener for when the fragment is finished & it is time to pass off the retrieved information to the firestore
    AddIngredientToRecipeFragment
    Fragment that handles adding a RecipeIngredient to a recipe.
    AddIngredientToRecipeFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener
    Listener for when the user is finished entering information and we can pass it back to the AddRecipeActivity.
    AddMealPlanFragment
    Fragment that handles adding a new MealPlan by the user.
    AddMealPlanFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener
    Interface that will allow the fragment to pass information back to the activity (and subsequently the Firebase)
    AddRecipeActivity
    Activity to handle adding a recipe
    ExampleInstrumentedTest
    Instrumented test, which will execute on an Android device.
    IngredientList
    Custom ArrayAdapter for displaying StorageIngredients.
    IngredientsActivity
    The activity that handles user interactions with their Storage Ingredients.
    IngredientsActivityTest
    Test class for features of the Ingredients activity
    IngredientsTest  
    MainActivity
    Activity that is displayed at the beginning of the app & that will direct the user to all the other activities & tabs
    MealPlanActivity
    The activity for viewing & interacting with the user's MealPlans.
    MealPlanActivityTest
    Test stories & functionality related to MealPlans activity Including: -> Adding a meal plan -> Making sure Meal Plans are visible ->
    MealPlanItem  
    MealPlanItemsList
    Class responsible for rendering the MealPlanItems within the app
    Recipe
    The recipe class is used to hold the user input data of the recipe which the user adds on when using the Recipe view and edit feature of the app.
    RecipeAdapter
    This class is responsible for making Recipes render-able on screen
    RecipeIngredient
    RecipeIngredient is used when the "quick add ingredient" from AddRecipeActivity is used
    RecipeIngredientListAdapter
    This class is responsible for rendering the list of RecipeIngredients of a particular Recipe (used inside of AddRecipeActivity)
    RecipesActivity
    Activity for user interacting with recipes.
    RecipesActivityTest  
    ShoppingList
    The ShoppingList class is responsible for generating a view of a shopping list item, based on an array of shopping list items
    ShoppingListActivity
    This activity will allow the user to navigate and manage their shopping cart, as well as mark items as purchased and add them to storage
    ShoppingListItem  
    ShowRecipeIngredientFragment
    This class is responsible for displaying the details of a RecipeIngredient as a DialogFragment
    ShowRecipeIngredientFragment.OnFragmentInteractionListener
    Functions handling Interactions with the RecipeIngredient (user may either click ok, and close the fragment, or they may choose to delete the ingredient)
    StorageIngredient
    Base class for the ingredients the user keeps in their storage.
    ViewIngredientFragment
    Fragment for handling viewing ingredients.
    ViewRecipeActivity
    This class allows the user to view the recipe, and all of the data/details that the recipe has
